      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Feeling of a Coup,'' by Anthony Lewis (column, March 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Feeling of a Coup,'' by Anthony Lewis (column, March 31):</p>
        <p>Mr. Lewis calls the current situation in our government by its rightful name: a coup.</p>
        <p>An election in which the disgraceful decisions of the Supreme Court ratified the trampling of constitutional principles of fair play has been followed by a rush to comply with the will of the corporate masters that put the administration in office.</p>
        <p>As a historian of 20th-century American history, I am well aware of the unprecedented nature of what is unfolding. Since George W. Bush and his allies showed so little respect for the fundamental precepts of our system in ''winning'' the election, it is not surprising to see them ignore international opinion with respect to global warming.</p>
        <p>When will the outrage begin to be expressed? Soon, I hope.</p>
        <p>GLENNA MATTHEWS  Berkeley, Calif., March 31, 2001</p>
      </block>
